OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1774137775
OL,3,CDying man pleads with Lords as poll
OL,4,Cshows public back assisted deaths
OL,6,FPolling conducted for ITV News by
OL,7,FIpsos of more than a thousand UK
OL,8,Fadults found 65% of respondents either
OL,9,Fstrongly support or tend to support
OL,10,Fthe assisted dying bill following more
OL,11,Fthan a year of debate in Westminster.
OL,13,FUK Editor Paul Brand has met with John
OL,14,FWilson and his family, who, in his
OL,15,Ffinal moments, is asking the House of
OL,16,FLords not to block a bill which would
OL,17,Flegalise assisted dying for people in
OL,18,Fhis situation.
OL,20,FJohn Wilson has had 75 rounds of
OL,21,Fchemotherapy and three major surgeries.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1774137775
OL,3,CDying man pleads with Lords as poll
OL,4,Cshows public back assisted deaths
OL,6,FThey have held back his terminal bowel
OL,7,Fcancer for six years, allowing him to
OL,8,Fwatch his children reach ages nine and
OL,9,F12.
OL,11,FBut by the time we meet, John's life
OL,12,Fis measured in weeks, perhaps days.
OL,14,F"I've lost an awful lot of weight," he
OL,15,Ftells me. "And, that physical change
OL,16,Fin particular has been very hard. I
OL,17,Fdon't really recognise myself in the
OL,18,Fmirror."
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@cO]wD@KOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1774137775
OL,3,CDying man pleads with Lords as poll
OL,4,Cshows public back assisted deaths
OL,6,FFrom his bed at Myton Hospice in
OL,7,FCoventry, we have been invited to film
OL,8,Fsome of his final moments, as he asks
OL,9,Fthe House of Lords not to block a bill
OL,10,Fwhich would legalise assisted dying
OL,11,Ffor people in his situation.
OL,13,F"Things are going to deteriorate," he
OL,14,Fsays. "The pain is going to increase.
OL,15,FI have said before, 'I'm sick of this
OL,16,Fand I wish there was a button I could
OL,17,Fpress'.
OL,19,F"Whether I'd actually come to do that
OL,20,For not, I'm not 100% sure, but I'd
OL,21,Fjust like to have the option."
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@bO]vD@GOU}D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1774137775
OL,3,CDying man pleads with Lords as poll
OL,4,Cshows public back assisted deaths
OL,6,F"I think it would have relieved so
OL,7,Fmuch anxiety over the years, but
OL,8,Fparticularly now," his wife Liz adds.
OL,10,F"Because you've had to deal with so
OL,11,Fmuch and you've fought so hard."
OL,13,F"You've got an incredible amount of
OL,14,Fstrength. But you've had a lot of
OL,15,Fthings taken away from you. I feel if
OL,16,Fyou had that choice, it would be one
OL,17,Fthing you'd have some element of
OL,18,Fcontrol over."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@RO]rD@AOUzD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
